node.text:
You become what you constantly feed your mind with.

If you constantly feed your mind with, “I can’t afford that, I can’t be rich, I can’t do that...”

Well guess what, you’re right.

Instead of telling yourself statements, which only closes the mind.

Change it to: “HOW can I afford that?”, “How can I be rich?”, “How can I do that?”. 

This will broaden your mind and you will start to think of solutions to your problem rather than excuses.

Did you find this helpful? Follow @savetoinvest for more!

#robertkiyosaki #moneymindset #richmindset #richmind #mindsetshift #changeyourmindset #savetoinvest

node.text:
We all wish we could go back to 2009 and buy a million Bitcoins for a few dollars.

Looking back, it seems surreal it has gone from nothing to $60,000 in a matter of a few years.⁠
⁠
The market cap for Bitcoin is now at $1 trillion, making it the 10th most valuable asset in the world.⁠
⁠
For reference, Google is worth $1.2T, Apple $2.2T, and Gold is $10T, but it took those a lot longer to get there compared to Bitcoin.
⁠
Obviously, we’ve missed the boat…right?⁠
⁠
Well, it depends.⁠
⁠
Nobody knows the future, but institutional investors are pouring in, retail investors are waking up and with an ever-shrinking supply, it could definitely go much higher.⁠
⁠
What do you think? Is it still too late? 🤔⁠
